{"questionId":"35030795","questionHtml":"<p>Determine how long it would take for the bacteria to fill the container.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER (find volume of all bacteria)</strong></p>\n<p>multiplying total population of bacteria by the volume of bacterium &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>18</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>5000</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>65</mn><mi>t</mi></msup><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>setting expression equal to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math> and attempt to solve (e.g. sketch) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR (find total number of bacteria to fill container)</strong></p>\n<p>attempting to find the total number of bacteria to fill container &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>18</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>18</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>13</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>setting value equal to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>S</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and attempt to solve (e.g. sketch) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: If <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>18</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;is seen but candidate has an incorrect total number of bacteria, the second <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> can still be awarded for setting their incorrect value equal to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>S</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and attempting to solve.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>hours</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2480</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35030795","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ2.3f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Determine how long it would take for the bacteria to fill the container.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.8—Use of technology to solve systems of linear equations and polynomial equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}